FBIS4-42245 "drweu105_l_94003" FBIS-WEU-94-105 Daily Report 29 May 1994 SPAIN ETA Demands Payment of Revolutionary Tax ETA Demands Payment of Revolutionary Tax LD2905165794 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network in Spanish 1600 GMT 29 May 94 LD2905165794 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network Spanish BFN [Text] ETA [Basque Fatherland and Liberty] is demanding between 10 and 15 million pesetas from businessmen and professionals in Guipuzcoa as payment of the revolutionary tax. This is what is reported today in LA VANGUARDIA. The newspaper says that the terrorist group is threatening Basque businessmen with reprisals should this latest attempt at extortion be reported to the police. The criminal organization says that it has complete personal data on these businessmen that will be used against them should they refuse to make payments.
